I"½<p>Commands to run a minimal docker container.<!--more--></p>

<p>cname is the name of our image and its tag. Stop and remove a container.</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>docker stop cname
docker container <span class="nb">rm </span>cname
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Build a container in the current directory.</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>docker build <span class="nt">--tag</span> cname <span class="nb">.</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Run a container.</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">export </span><span class="nv">PORT</span><span class="o">=</span>8080
docker run <span class="nt">-d</span> <span class="nt">-p</span> <span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">PORT</span><span class="k">}</span>:<span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">PORT</span><span class="k">}</span> <span class="nt">--name</span> cname cname
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Run an image with an interactive shell.</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>docker run <span class="nt">-it</span> cname bash
</code></pre></div></div>

<h4 id="makefile">Makefile</h4>

<p>It is convinient to organize this shit in a Makefile.</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>PORT :<span class="o">=</span> 8080

dev:
  docker run <span class="nt">-it</span> cname bash

run:
  docker run <span class="nt">-d</span> <span class="nt">-p</span> <span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">PORT</span><span class="k">}</span>:<span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">PORT</span><span class="k">}</span> <span class="nt">--name</span> cname cname
  
build:
  docker build <span class="nt">--tag</span> cname <span class="nb">.</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
